Basic JavaScript: Use Multiple Conditional (Ternary) Operators

Use multiple conditional operators in the checkSign function to check if a number
is positive, negative or zero. The function should return "positive", "negative" or "zero".

function checkSign(num) {

}

checkSign(10);

// Solution 

function checkSign(num) {
    return (num === 0) ? "zero"  : (num > 0) ?  "positive" :  "negative"
  } 
